<h1 class="post-title entry-title">Betty &#8211; The Siri-like Commandline Virtual Assistant For Linux</h1>
<p class="post-byline">by <span class="vcard author">
<span class="fn"><a href="https://www.ostechnix.com/author/sk/" title="Posts by sk" rel="author">sk</a></span>
</span> &middot;
Published <time class="published" datetime="August 17, 2017">August 17, 2017</time>
&middot; Updated <time class="updated" datetime="August 20, 2018">August 20, 2018</time>
</p>
<div class="post-format">
<div class="image-container">
<img width="720" height="340" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" data-src="https://www.ostechnix.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Betty-The-Siri-like-Commandline-Virtual-Assistant-1-720x340.png" class="attachment-thumb-large size-thumb-large wp-post-image" alt="Betty - The Siri-like Commandline Virtual Assistant for Linux" data-srcset="https://www.ostechnix.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Betty-The-Siri-like-Commandline-Virtual-Assistant-1-720x340.png 720w, https://www.ostechnix.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Betty-The-Siri-like-Commandline-Virtual-Assistant-1-520x245.png 520w" data-sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px" /> </div>
</div>
